                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> BERKHAMPSTEAD. Convention (indented) made the Saturday next after the feast of
                  the Assumption of the B.V.M., <origDate notBefore="1255-10-28" notAfter="1256-10-27">40 Hen. III</origDate>, by which 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Bernard</forename> 
                           <surname>fitz-Ralph</surname>
                        </persName> lets to
                  farm to <persName nymRef="Gossalmer">
                           <forename>John</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Adam</forename> 
                              <surname>Gossalmer</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  the whole of his part of the capital messuage, mill, &amp;c., which were
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Osbert</forename> le <surname>Ster</surname>
                        </persName>'s in
                  <placeName key="place_1083318">Berchamstede, in the parish of Norh.</placeName> at an annual rent of 28s. 
                   </p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
